00:10:07.670 --> 00:10:11.090
So the bellows,
how do they work?

00:10:11.090 --> 00:10:13.850
Basically an accordion, not
this because it's electric,

00:10:13.850 --> 00:10:18.362
but an acoustic accordion
basically works as a harmonica.

00:10:18.362 --> 00:10:19.820
In fact in Italian,
the accordion's

00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:21.590
called the fisarmonica.

00:10:21.590 --> 00:10:23.570
All it is is these
big harmonicas

00:10:23.570 --> 00:10:25.910
that you can actually pull
them out and play them.

00:10:25.910 --> 00:10:28.010
And they just all
have reeds on them.

00:10:28.010 --> 00:10:30.250
And they are put here and here.

00:10:30.250 --> 00:10:32.340
And they're connected to
the air in the bellows

00:10:32.340 --> 00:10:34.280
and they're connected
to the keys.

00:10:34.280 --> 00:10:39.280
And when you hit a note what
happens is, the hammer opens.

00:10:39.280 --> 00:10:42.580
And then when you pull air
through that reed plays.

00:10:42.580 --> 00:10:44.380
So that's really--
it's just a harmonica

00:10:44.380 --> 00:10:47.560
with a lot of buttons on it,
pretty much-- many harmonicas.

00:10:47.560 --> 00:10:51.660
And the different registers
here just have different sounds.

00:10:51.660 --> 00:10:55.990
So if I just go to a straight
accordion here, and just

00:10:55.990 --> 00:10:56.845
play a note.

