No one's ever been able to
[INAUDIBLE] the picture.

00:52:04.320 --> 00:52:06.153
Apparently in Turkey,
where microtonal music

00:52:06.153 --> 00:52:09.870
you see a lot with the
[INAUDIBLE] and such.

00:52:09.870 --> 00:52:11.070
What's the scales?

00:52:11.070 --> 00:52:16.180
I can't think--
those Turkish scales.

00:52:16.180 --> 00:52:16.680
Makams!

00:52:16.680 --> 00:52:17.990
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:52:17.990 --> 00:52:20.820
There are accordions they
make with semi-tone notes,

00:52:20.820 --> 00:52:21.844
and they're split up.

00:52:21.844 --> 00:52:23.510
And I've heard this
from multiple people

00:52:23.510 --> 00:52:24.140
that they exist.

00:52:24.140 --> 00:52:25.306
I have yet to see a picture.

00:52:25.306 --> 00:52:27.100
But apparently they
do, because there's

00:52:27.100 --> 00:52:29.670
some pretty reputable sources.

00:52:29.670 --> 00:52:32.100
So not on this one, although
I can actually come in here

00:52:32.100 --> 00:52:33.849
and tweak the tuning
and things like that.

00:52:33.849 --> 00:52:38.760
But I can't have certain
notes be different things.

00:52:38.760 --> 00:52:40.920
So not this one, no.

00:52:40.920 --> 00:52:43.370
But apparently
you can somewhere.

